'''Garry Mendes Rodrigues''' ({{IPA|pt|ɡa.ˈʀi ˈmẽ.dɨʒ ʀu.ˈdɾi.ɡɨʃ|lang}}; born 27 November 1990) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Cypriot First Division]] club [[Apollon Limassol FC|Apollon Limassol]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

In February 2013, Rodrigues announced that he would like to represent Cape Verde,<ref>{{cite web|title=Garry Mendes Rodrigues interview|url=http://www.criolosports.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3043%3Aenglish-featured-athlete-garry-mendes-rodrigues&catid=46%3Afeatured-athlete&Itemid=93|publisher=Criolo Sports|access-date=25 February 2013}}</ref> and made his debut in August 2013.<ref name=IntDebut>[http://desporto.sapo.cv/futebol/mais/amigaveis_seleccoes/epoca-2013/jogos/50307 Cape Verde vs. Gabon report] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150702100114/http://desporto.sapo.cv/futebol/mais/amigaveis_seleccoes/epoca-2013/jogos/50307 |date=2 July 2015 }} {{in lang|pt}}</ref> He represented the side at the [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations|2015]] and [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations|2021]] [[Africa Cup of Nations]].

He formerly played for [[PAOK FC|PAOK]], [[Elche CF]], [[XerxesDZB]], FC Boshuizen, [[ADO Den Haag]], [[FC Dordrecht|Dordrecht]], [[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]] and [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]].

He is a cousin of [[Jerson Cabral]].

==Club career==
As a youth player Rodrigues played for [[Feyenoord]] and Portuguese [[Real Sport Clube]].{{citation needed|date=July 2025}}

Rodrigues joined [[Eredivisie]] club [[ADO Den Haag]] from amateur FC Boshuizen on 16 May 2012, signing a 1+1 years contract.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=groengeelhart.nl|title=Garry Mendes Rodrigues tekent contract bij ADO Den Haag|url=http://www.groengeelhart.nl/?p=nieuws&nid=2315|date=16 May 2012|language=nl}}</ref> In July, he was loaned out to [[Eerste Divisie]] club [[FC Dordrecht|Dordrecht]]. Rodrigues made his league debut in a 1–1 away draw against [[FC Emmen|Emmen]] on 10 August, playing the full 90 minutes.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=groengeelhart.nl|title=Emmen 1–1 Dordrecht|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/08/10/netherlands/eerste-divisie/fc-emmen/bvo-fc-dordrecht/1290750/|date=10 August 2012}}</ref>

===Levski Sofia===
On 11 February 2013, Rodrigues signed a two-and-a-half-year contract with Bulgarian club [[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=gong.bg|title=Гари Родригес подписа с Левски|url=http://www.gong.bg/view_article.php?article_id=327657|date=11 February 2013|language=bg}}</ref> He made his debut away at [[PSFC Chernomorets Burgas|Chernomorets Burgas]] in a 2–0 win on 3 March. On 13 March, he scored his first goal for Levski in the 22nd minute of a [[Bulgarian Cup]] quarter-final first leg tie against [[PFC Litex Lovech|Litex Lovech]].<ref>{{cite web|website=Soccerway|title=Levski Sofia 1–0 Litex Lovech|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/03/13/bulgaria/cup/pfc-levski-sofia/pfk-litex-lovech/1423481/|date=13 March 2013}}</ref> On 20 April, in a 2–1 away victory over Litex, Rodrigues netted his first league goal and assisted [[Hristo Yovov]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=gong.bg|title=Левски прекъсна черната серия в Ловеч|url=http://gong.bg/view_article.php?article_id=341811|date=20 April 2013|language=bg}}</ref>

On 21 July 2013, Rodrigues opened the scoring in Levski's first match of the [[2013–14 A PFG]] season against [[PFC Botev Plovdiv|Botev Plovdiv]], but was subsequently [[sent off]] after an altercation with [[Veselin Minev]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=topsport.bg|title=Феноменален Неделев обърна "Левски", "Ботев" удари "сините" с 2:1
|url=http://topsport.ibox.bg/material/id_1738770894|date=21 July 2013|language=bg}}</ref>

During the first half of the 2013–14 season Rodrigues scored 14 goals in total helping Levski Sofia to overcome several teams and progress to the 3rd place in the league ranking. He also scored a penalty in the 7–6 win after penalties against [[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]] in a Bulgarian Cup Eternal Derby third round tie, eventually helping the team to reach the quarter-finals of the competition. The strong overall performance led to the interest of several European clubs. In January 2014, [[West Ham United]] sent an offer to Levski for a trial, but Rodrigues refused it, stating that he would only negotiate with a team which is guaranteed to offer him a contract.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=topsport.bg|title=Йовов смъмри Родригес, навива го за пробите, холандецът си спечели сърдити погледи от шефовете|url=http://topsport.ibox.bg/news/id_1001722050|date=13 January 2014 |language=bg}}</ref>

===Elche===
On 27 January 2014, Rodrigues signed with [[Elche CF]] on a six-month loan through Promoesport (an investment fund linked to [[Gimnàstic de Tarragona]]), with a buyout clause.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/news/soccer-levski-winger-rodrigues-joins-elche-150230354--sow.html|publisher=sports.yahoo.com|title=Levski winger Rodrigues joins Elche|date=27 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elchediario.com/display.aspx?id=13013|title=Garry Rodrigues viene cedido por parte del Nàstic de Tarragona|trans-title=Garry Rodrigues comes on loan from ''Nàstic'' de Tarragona|publisher=Elche Diario|language=es|date=3 February 2014|access-date=8 March 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222035727/http://www.elchediario.com/display.aspx?id=13013|archive-date=22 February 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his [[La Liga]] debut on 1 March, coming on as a second-half substitute in the 1–0 home win over [[Celta de Vigo]],<ref>{{cite web|publisher=flashscore.com|title=Elche 1-0 Celta Vigo|url=http://www.flashscore.com/match/bk50mJpr/#match-summary|date=1 March 2014}}</ref> and scored his first goal in the category on 3 May, netting the game's only in an away success against [[Málaga CF]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/311000/report |title=Away-day joy for Elche |publisher=Sky Sports |date=3 May 2014 |access-date=28 May 2014}}</ref>

In the 2014 summer Rodrigues signed a four-year deal with the [[Valencian Community|Valencian]] club, after his buyout clause was activated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://diariofranjiverde.com/rodrigues-gordo-tarragona/|title=Garry Rodrigues deja 'el gordo' en Tarragona|trans-title=Garry Rodrigues leaves 'the lottery' in Tarragona|publisher=Diario Franjiverde|language=es|date=20 December 2014|access-date=8 March 2015|archive-date=7 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180807064128/https://diariofranjiverde.com/rodrigues-gordo-tarragona/|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 31 July 2015, he rescinded his link.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elchecf.es/-/garry-rodrigues-abandona-el-elche-c-f-|title=Garry Rodrigues abandona el Elche C.F.|trans-title=Garry Rodrigues leaves Elche C.F.|language=es|date=31 July 2015|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804000513/http://www.elchecf.es/-/garry-rodrigues-abandona-el-elche-c-f-|archive-date=4 August 2015}}</ref>

===PAOK===
On 4 August 2015, Rodrigues signed a three-year contract with [[PAOK FC|PAOK]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sport24.gr/football/omades/Paok/anakoinwse-rontrigkes-o-paok.3603457.html |title=Ανακοίνωσε Ροντρίγκες ο ΠΑΟΚ|publisher = www.sport24.gr|date=4 August 2015}}</ref> On 23 September 2015, in a home derby game against [[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]] he scored his first goal in Greek [[Super League]]. On 11 January 2016, PAOK turned down [[Al-Ahli Saudi FC]]'s offer in the region of €1.7 million for Garry Rodrigues.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdna.gr/news-english/article/155465/paok-reject-al-ahly-bid-garry-rodrigues |title=PAOK reject Al-Ahly bid for Garry Rodrigues |publisher = www.sdna.gr |date=11 January 2016}}</ref> He finished the season with seven goals being the third scorer of the club.

On 24 November 2016, in a [[UEFA Europa League]] group stage away match against [[ACF Fiorentina]], Rodrigues scored a late goal to give PAOK a 3–2 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdna.gr/podosfairo/europa-league/article/268218/fiorentina-paok-2-3-vids |title=Φιορεντίνα-ΠΑΟΚ 2-3 |publisher = www.sdna.gr |date=24 November 2016}}</ref>

===Galatasaray===
On 9 January 2017, PAOK officially announced the transfer of Rodrigues to Galatasaray for a fee of €3.7 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sabah.com.tr/spor/futbol/2017/01/09/paok-resmen-acikladi-garry-rodriguesin-galatasaraya-transferi-tamamlandi |title=PAOK resmen açıkladı: Garry Rodrigues'in Galatasaray'a transferi tamamlandı |publisher = www.sabah.com.tr |date=9 January 2017}}</ref> In February 2018, he was linked with a move to [[Olympique Lyon|Lyon]], having scored five goals and made eight assists in 22 Süper Lig appearances since the start of the 2017–18 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://africanfootball.com/news/743400/Olympique-Lyon-keen-on-Garry-Rodrigues |title=OLYMPIQUE LYON KEEN ON GARRY RODRIGUES |publisher = africanfootball.com |date=26 February 2018}}</ref>

He was contracted to Galatasaray until the summer of 2021.

===Al-Ittihad===
On 6 January 2019, Rodrigues joined Al-Ittihad of [[Saudi Arabia]] for a fee of €9m.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fanatik.com.tr/galatasarayda-garry-rodrigues-al-ittihada-transfer-oldu-2035887 |title=Galatasaray'da Garry Rodrigues Al İttihad'a transfer oldu |publisher = www.fanatik.com.tr |date=6 January 2019}}</ref>

===Fenerbahçe===
On 13 July 2019, [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] announced the signing of Rodrigues on loan for 2 years from Al-Ittihad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2019/7/garry-rodrigues-fenerbahcemizde |title=Garry Rodrigues Fenerbahçemizde |publisher = fenerbahce.org |date=13 July 2019}}</ref>

===Olympiacos===
On 18 September 2021, [[Olympiacos F.C.]] officially announced the signing of Rodrigues on a three-year contract with €1 million annual fee, including bonuses.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gazzetta.gr/football/superleague/2043654/olympiakos-anakoinose-ton-gkari-rontrigkes-pic |title=Ολυμπιακός: Ανακοίνωσε τον Γκάρι Ροντρίγκες! |publisher = www.gazzetta.gr |date=18 September 2021}}</ref>

===Ankaragücü===
On 19 August 2023, he signed a two-year contract with [[Süper Lig]] club [[MKE Ankaragücü|Ankaragücü]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ankaragucu.org.tr/garry-rodrigues-ankaragucumuzde/|title=Garry Rodrigues Ankaragücü'müzde|last=|first=|date=19 August 2023|website=ankaragucu.org.tr|publisher=|language=tr|access-date=26 August 2023}}</ref>

==International career==
Rodrigues received his first international call-up in August 2013 to play friendly match against [[Gabon national football team|Gabon]] on the 14th of that month.<ref>{{cite web|title=Garry estreia-se no regresso de Ryan e Fernando Varela|language=pt|trans-title=Garry debuts in the return of Ryan and Fernando Varela|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/seleccao/cabo-verde/tubaroes/artigo/2013/08/05/garry_estreia_se_no_regresso_de_.html|publisher=SAPO Desporto|access-date=15 August 2013|archive-date=2 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140102190909/http://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/seleccao/cabo-verde/tubaroes/artigo/2013/08/05/garry_estreia_se_no_regresso_de_.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> He [[Substitute (association football)|substituted]] [[Djaniny]] at halftime.<ref name=IntDebut/> On 30 December 2013, Rodrigues appeared as a starter in the 1–4 loss against [[Catalonia national football team|Catalonia]] in a [[friendly match]], assisting his team's goal that was scored by Djaniny.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=futbol.univision.com|title=Cataluña 4-1 Cabo Verde: Cataluña sentencia a Cabo Verde en tres minutos|url=http://futbol.univision.com/europa/calendario/article/2013-12-30/cataluna-4-cabo-verde-1-amistoso-cronica#axzz2sBZqCneU|date=30 December 2013|language=es}}</ref> On 6 September 2014 he scored his first international goal in a 3–1 away win over [[Niger national football team|Niger]] in Cape Verde's successful qualification for the [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations]]. Rodrigues was included in their squad for the finals in [[Equatorial Guinea]], but due to competition from [[Kuca Miranda|Kuca]], Djaniny and [[Júlio Tavares]] he played only in the goalless draw with [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]], which confirmed their elimination from [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations Group B|Group B]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Cape Verde Islands 1-1 Zambia|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30875465|access-date=7 April 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=16 January 2015}}</ref>

In January 2022, Rodrigues was a member of the Cape Verde squad that represented the nation at the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/59763245|title=Afcon 2021: Ethiopia and Cape Verde squads for finals in Cameroon|date=23 December 2021|access-date=21 January 2024|website=BBC Sport Africa}}</ref> He appeared in all four of the team's matches, assisting [[Júlio Tavares]]' winning goal in their opening fixture against [[Ethiopia national football team|Ethiopia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/sport/20220109-cape-verde-sink-10-man-ethiopia-in-africa-cup-of-nations-surprise|title=Cape Verde sink 10-man Ethiopia in Africa Cup of Nations surprise|date=9 January 2022|access-date=21 January 2024|website=France 24}}</ref> and scoring the equaliser in a 1–1 draw with host nation [[Cameroon national football team|Cameroon]] which ensured their qualification to the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations knockout stage|knockout stage]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.france24.com/en/sport/20220117-live-tournament-hosts-and-hot-prospects-cameroon-take-on-cape-verde|title=As it happened: Cape Verde fight back to hold Cameroon to surprise 1-1 draw|date=17 January 2022|access-date=21 January 2024|website=France 24}}</ref>

In December 2023, Rodrigues was named in Cape Verde's squad for his third [[Africa Cup of Nations]] – the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations|2023 tournament]] in the [[Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/cape-verde-name-veterans-mendes-vozinha-african-cup-nations-squad-2023-12-29/|title=Cape Verde name veterans Mendes, Vozinha in African Cup of Nations squad|date=30 December 2023|access-date=21 January 2023|website=Reuters}}</ref> On 14 January 2024, in Cape Verde's opening match against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]], he scored a 92nd minute goal to give the ''Tubarões Azuis'' a 2–1 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67904849|title=Ghana 1-2 Cape Verde - Black Stars fall to late defeat|date=14 January 2024|access-date=21 January 2024|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

